The overall event showcased a mix of positive and challenging aspects. Venue and facilities generally met expectations to some extent, but issues such as cleanliness and toilets, logistic delays , delayed breaks, occasional issues with necessary materials, temperature control , technical difficulties were noted in specific rooms. Sessions adhered to schedules, but minor delays occurred between session . Facilitators demonstrated varying communication effectiveness, with concerns about authority in one case.Participants were attentive, and there was active peer learning and discussion in many sessions. Consistency in facilitator engagement and a more proactive approach to resolving technical challenges would contribute to an overall enhanced learning experience.

The training program exhibited strengths in venue arrangements, audiovisual equipment, and facilitator engagement. However, challenges were noted in room cleanliness and temperature control. Timeliness was generally maintained, but improvements are needed in breaks and session consistency. The facilitators demonstrated strengths in communication, friendliness, and overall confidence. They effectively used visuals and engaged participants, but some struggled with complex concepts and consistent content delivery. The content was relevant, and efforts were made for gender inclusion however gender - balanced participation was a challenge. Overall, the program displayed positive elements but would benefit from refining logistical aspects, maintaining consistency, and optimizing participant engagement strategies.
